 2) 1, 3 and any of the four digits: 6, 7, 8 and 9;
 N2 = 4n = 4 * 6 = 24.
 3) 1, 4 and any of the two digits: 8 and 9;
 N3 = 2n = 2 * 6 = 12.
 4) 2, 4 and any of the two digits: 8 and 9;
 N4 = 2n = 2 * 6 = 12.
 The number of all three-digit numbers will then be: N = N1 + N2 + N3 + N4 = 36 + 24 + 12 + 12 = 84.
 Answer: 84

